text: Tinatin Bokuchava (born 29 May 1983) is a Georgian politician, Member of United National Movement. She is a Member of Parliament of Georgia since 2012. She studied at Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy. In 2011 - at Smith College. From 2009 to 2011 she worked in National-Democratic Institute. She is a Leader of women's wing of United National Movement. ==References== Category:1983 births Category:Members of the Parliament of Georgia Category:Politicians from Tbilisi Category:Living people
